Build me a Progressive Web App (PWA) chat interface called "Gerald" — a frontend for a local AI agent running on my home server.

WHAT IT DOES:
The app sends user messages to a webhook endpoint and displays Gerald's responses. All conversation is in-memory (no persistence needed). It should feel like a polished, finished product — not a dev tool.

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- Single HTML file (index.html) with all CSS and JS inline — no build step, no dependencies except one font from Google Fonts
- POST messages to a configurable webhook URL (set as a const at the top of the file: const WEBHOOK_URL = "http://your-server-ip:5679/webhook/gerald")
- Request format: POST with JSON body { "chatInput": "user message here", "sessionId": "gerald-ui-[timestamp]" }
- Display the response from the JSON field "output"
- Session ID generated once on page load and reused for the whole session
- PWA manifest embedded inline (as a blob URL) so it can be installed to home screen
- Service worker for offline shell (just show "Gerald is offline" if no connection)
- Mobile-first responsive layout that also works on desktop

DESIGN DIRECTION — dark, terminal-inspired, minimal:
- Dark background (#0d0d0d or similar near-black)
- Monospace font for Gerald's responses (suggest JetBrains Mono from Google Fonts), clean sans-serif for user messages
- Colour accent: a single muted green (#4ade80 or similar) used sparingly — Gerald's name, the status dot, send button hover
- Header: "Gerald" in the accent colour, small green pulsing dot showing he's online, subtle version label "v2.0"
- Message bubbles: user messages right-aligned with a subtle dark surface background, Gerald's responses left-aligned, no bubble — just text with the monospace font
- Thinking indicator: three animated dots in the accent colour while waiting for response
- Input bar pinned to bottom, full-width text input, send on Enter or button click
- No avatars, no timestamps, no unnecessary chrome — maximum focus on the conversation

BEHAVIOUR:
- Disable input and show thinking indicator while waiting for response
- If the request fails, show an inline error message styled as a Gerald response: "Connection failed. Is the server running?"
- Auto-scroll to latest message
- Input clears after sending
- On mobile, input should not cause the page to scroll behind the keyboard

PWA:
- App name: "Gerald"
- Short name: "Gerald"
- Display: standalone
- Theme colour: #0d0d0d
- Background colour: #0d0d0d
- Include a simple SVG icon (a stylised "G" in the accent green on dark background) embedded as a data URI

WHAT NOT TO DO:
- No React, no Vue, no build tools
- No external API calls except to the webhook
- No localStorage or cookies
- No sidebar, no conversation history list, no settings panel — keep it brutally simple
- No purple gradients, no generic AI chatbot aesthetic

Deliver a single index.html file. Add a comment at the top explaining the only thing the user needs to change is the WEBHOOK_URL constant.
